avWlanMobAgentVlanTable.name: avWlanMobAgentVlanTable
avWlanMobAgentVlanTable.description: This is the configuration table for mobility VLANs.

avWlanMobAgentVlanEntry.name: avWlanMobAgentVlanEntry
avWlanMobAgentVlanEntry.description: Configuration settings for a mobility VLAN.

avWlanMobAgentVlanName.name: avWlanMobAgentVlanName
avWlanMobAgentVlanName.description: This object uniquely identifies a mobility VLAN.

avWlanMobAgentVlanLVID.name: avWlanMobAgentVlanLVID
avWlanMobAgentVlanLVID.description: The local VLAN ID. This maps the global VLAN to a locally defined VLAN.

avWlanMobAgentVlanL3Mobility.name: avWlanMobAgentVlanL3Mobility
avWlanMobAgentVlanL3Mobility.description: This object indicates the L3 mobility mode for the VLAN. The meaning of the values is: none(1) - L3 mobility is not enabled for this VLAN (L2 mobility is supported, which is the default behaviour when a VLAN is mapped). server(2) - L3 mobility is enabled for this VLAN, and this switch can act as a server for this mobility VLAN. The rest of the parameters for the VLAN are valid. client(3) - L3 mobility is enabled for this VLAN, and this switch is configured as a static client for this VLAN. All ports in the mapped Local VLAN will be remotely connected to this mobility VLAN.

avWlanMobAgentVlanWeight.name: avWlanMobAgentVlanWeight
avWlanMobAgentVlanWeight.description: This object specifies a weight value to be used to compute the priority used to determine the winning server amongst a number of switches configured as server for this VLAN.

avWlanMobAgentVlanTrack.name: avWlanMobAgentVlanTrack
avWlanMobAgentVlanTrack.description: The objects specifies a list of ports whose status will be tracked to determine the priority used to elect the VLAN server for this VLAN. This list must be a subset of the member ports of the local VLAN mapped to this mobility VLAN. The default value for this object is the complete set of member ports of the local VLAN.

avWlanMobAgentVlanWcValidated.name: avWlanMobAgentVlanWcValidated
avWlanMobAgentVlanWcValidated.description: Indicates whether the Mobility VLAN name for this entry was received from (and thus validated by) the managing controller. Mostly useful for validating mappings that were manually added offline before the switch associated to the controller.

avWlanMobAgentVlanAdminMapped.name: avWlanMobAgentVlanAdminMapped
avWlanMobAgentVlanAdminMapped.description: Indicates whether the LVID mapping for this entry was set by admin or auto-assigned by the switch itself. Has no meaning if the LVID value is 0

avWlanMobAgentVlanActive.name: avWlanMobAgentVlanActive
avWlanMobAgentVlanActive.description: Indicates whether the LVID mapping is in 'Active' state. For mapping to be 'Active', the following conditions have to be satisfied: - Mobility VLAN has to be received from (validated by) WC. - LVID element has to be mapped a value other than 0. - LVID has to represent a valid local VLAN on this switch.

avWlanMobAgentVlanRowStatus.name: avWlanMobAgentVlanRowStatus
avWlanMobAgentVlanRowStatus.description: This variable is used to create or delete entries in the table. Only the entries manually added offline that have not (yet) been 'validated' by the managing Controller can be deleted from this table.

avWlanMobSwLocalDeviceId.name: avWlanMobSwLocalDeviceId
avWlanMobSwLocalDeviceId.description: This object contains the MAC address that uniquely identifies the local mobility switch. This value is what is used to identify this switch in peer switches and controllers, and is used as an index value in various MIBs to identify entries that pertain to the local switch.

avWlanMobSwAllStatisticsReset.name: avWlanMobSwAllStatisticsReset
avWlanMobSwAllStatisticsReset.description: When we set this object to reset, all the statistics for every tunnel will be cleared. Read on this object will always return none.

avWlanMobSwAllStatisticsResetStatus.name: avWlanMobSwAllStatisticsResetStatus
avWlanMobSwAllStatisticsResetStatus.description: This object indicates the current status of the switch statistics reset request. Default value is not started.

avWlanMobSwCtrlAddrType.name: avWlanMobSwCtrlAddrType
avWlanMobSwCtrlAddrType.description: The type of internet address contained in the corresponding instance of avWlanMobSwCtrlAddr. Currently only ipv4(1) and ipv6(2) are allowed.

avWlanMobSwCtrlAddr.name: avWlanMobSwCtrlAddr
avWlanMobSwCtrlAddr.description: The System internet address of the controller that is managing this mobility switch. The type of address contained in this object is indicated by the corresponding instance of avWlanMobSwCtrlAddrType.

avWlanMobSwNumMobilityTunnels.name: avWlanMobSwNumMobilityTunnels
avWlanMobSwNumMobilityTunnels.description: The current number of Mobility tunnels establisted on this switch.

avWlanMobSwNumAccessTunnels.name: avWlanMobSwNumAccessTunnels
avWlanMobSwNumAccessTunnels.description: The current number of Access tunnels establisted on this switch.

avWlanMobSwNumResPeerAccessTunnels.name: avWlanMobSwNumResPeerAccessTunnels
avWlanMobSwNumResPeerAccessTunnels.description: The current number of Access tunnels establisted on this switch that are managed by its resiliency peer. Initially intended for switches running as SMLT pairs.

avWlanMobSwFdbGlobalFlushAction.name: avWlanMobSwFdbGlobalFlushAction
avWlanMobSwFdbGlobalFlushAction.description: When we set this object to flushAll(2), all the FDB entries learned by mobility switch will be flushed. Read on this object will always return none.

avWlanMobSwFdbGlobalFlushActionStatus.name: avWlanMobSwFdbGlobalFlushActionStatus
avWlanMobSwFdbGlobalFlushActionStatus.description: This object indicates the current status of flushing all fdb entries learned by the mobility swithc request. Default value is not started.

avWlanMobSwPurgeInactiveMaps.name: avWlanMobSwPurgeInactiveMaps
avWlanMobSwPurgeInactiveMaps.description: Setting this object would purge all the inactive mappings from the mobility agent vlan table (avWlanMobAgentVlanTable) ie entries whose value of avWlanMobAgentVlanActive is False. Read from this field always returns none (1).

avWlanMobSwDeviceTable.name: avWlanMobSwDeviceTable
avWlanMobSwDeviceTable.description: Despite the somewhat misleading name, this table contains status entries of the Access and Mobility tunnels that are established at the local switch.

avWlanMobSwDeviceEntry.name: avWlanMobSwDeviceEntry
avWlanMobSwDeviceEntry.description: A peer mobility switch or an access point.

avWlanMobSwDeviceId.name: avWlanMobSwDeviceId
avWlanMobSwDeviceId.description: The MAC address that uniquely identifies the peer mobility switch or access point on the other side of the tunnel.

avWlanMobSwDeviceAddrType.name: avWlanMobSwDeviceAddrType
avWlanMobSwDeviceAddrType.description: This object indicates the type of internet address in the corresponding instance of avWlanMobSwDeviceAddr. Currently, only the values ipv4(1) and ipv6(2) are allowed.

avWlanMobSwDeviceAddr.name: avWlanMobSwDeviceAddr
avWlanMobSwDeviceAddr.description: The address of the peer mobility switch or access point. The type of address is indicated by the corresponding instance of avWlanMobSwDeviceAddrType.

avWlanMobSwDeviceUdpPort.name: avWlanMobSwDeviceUdpPort
avWlanMobSwDeviceUdpPort.description: Indicates the UDP port which the peer mobility switch or access point will use for control protocol communication with the local switch.

avWlanMobSwDeviceStatus.name: avWlanMobSwDeviceStatus
avWlanMobSwDeviceStatus.description: Indicates the status of the mobility tunnel connection to this peer mobility switch, or the access tunnel to this access point.

avWlanMobSwDeviceLocalUdpPort.name: avWlanMobSwDeviceLocalUdpPort
avWlanMobSwDeviceLocalUdpPort.description: Indicates the local UDP port through which the current Mobility Tunnel(or Resiliency Tunnel) or Access Tunnel is connected.

avWlanMobSwDeviceInterfaceId.name: avWlanMobSwDeviceInterfaceId
avWlanMobSwDeviceInterfaceId.description: Used to display Logical Port for the tunnel.

avWlanMobPeerVlansAdvertisedTable.name: avWlanMobPeerVlansAdvertisedTable
avWlanMobPeerVlansAdvertisedTable.description: This table contains a list of the Mobility VLANs that are advertised by each peer Mobility Switch with which the local mobility switch has established a mobility tunnel.

avWlanMobPeerVlansAdvertisedEntry.name: avWlanMobPeerVlansAdvertisedEntry
avWlanMobPeerVlansAdvertisedEntry.description: A mobility vlan advertised by a peer mobility switch.

avWlanMobPeerVlansAdvertisedId.name: avWlanMobPeerVlansAdvertisedId
avWlanMobPeerVlansAdvertisedId.description: The MAC address that uniquely identifies the peer mobility switch.

avWlanMobPeerVlansAdvertisedVlanName.name: avWlanMobPeerVlansAdvertisedVlanName
avWlanMobPeerVlansAdvertisedVlanName.description: This object indicates the name of the advertised mobility VLAN.

avWlanMobPeerVlansAdvertisedPriority.name: avWlanMobPeerVlansAdvertisedPriority
avWlanMobPeerVlansAdvertisedPriority.description: This object indicates the priority of the advertised mobility VLAN.

avWlanMobVlanServerTable.name: avWlanMobVlanServerTable
avWlanMobVlanServerTable.description: This table contains the currently selected server for each mobility vlan.

avWlanMobVlanServerEntry.name: avWlanMobVlanServerEntry
avWlanMobVlanServerEntry.description: A mobility vlan advertised by a peer mobility switch.

avWlanMobVlanServerVlanName.name: avWlanMobVlanServerVlanName
avWlanMobVlanServerVlanName.description: This object identifies the mobility vlan.

avWlanMobVlanServerId.name: avWlanMobVlanServerId
avWlanMobVlanServerId.description: This object identifies the currently selected server for this mobility vlan. Note that the internet address and status of this server can be retrieved from the corresponding entry in the avWlanMobSwDeviceTable.

avWlanMobVlanServerPriority.name: avWlanMobVlanServerPriority
avWlanMobVlanServerPriority.description: This object indicates the priority of the VLAN.

avWlanMobVlanPeerAdvertiserTable.name: avWlanMobVlanPeerAdvertiserTable
avWlanMobVlanPeerAdvertiserTable.description: This table contains a list of all peer mobility switches that are advertising each mobility vlan.

avWlanMobVlanPeerAdvertiserEntry.name: avWlanMobVlanPeerAdvertiserEntry
avWlanMobVlanPeerAdvertiserEntry.description: A mobility switch that is advertising a particular mobility vlan.

avWlanMobVlanPeerAdvertiserVlanName.name: avWlanMobVlanPeerAdvertiserVlanName
avWlanMobVlanPeerAdvertiserVlanName.description: This object identifies the mobility vlan.

avWlanMobVlanPeerAdvertiserId.name: avWlanMobVlanPeerAdvertiserId
avWlanMobVlanPeerAdvertiserId.description: This object identifies a peer mobility switch that is advertising this mobility vlan. Note that the internet address and status of this peer can be retrieved from the corresponding entry in the avWlanMobSwDeviceTable.

avWlanMobVlanPeerAdvertiserPriority.name: avWlanMobVlanPeerAdvertiserPriority
avWlanMobVlanPeerAdvertiserPriority.description: This object indicates the priority of the VLAN.

avWlanMobSwTunnelIpAddress.name: avWlanMobSwTunnelIpAddress

avWlanMobSwTunnelInterfaceId.name: avWlanMobSwTunnelInterfaceId

avWlanMobSwControllerAddrType.name: avWlanMobSwControllerAddrType

avWlanMobSwControllerAddr.name: avWlanMobSwControllerAddr

avWlanMobSwControllerRowStatus.name: avWlanMobSwControllerRowStatus

avWlanMobSwFdbTable.description: This table contains FDB entries for wireless traffic.

avWlanMobSwFdbEntry.name: avWlanMobSwFdbEntry
avWlanMobSwFdbEntry.description: Information about a specific unicast MAC address for which the mobility switch has forwarding information.

avWlanMobSwFdbMacAddress.name: avWlanMobSwFdbMacAddress

avWlanMobSwFdbType.name: avWlanMobSwFdbType
